# Adding a New Trip Blog Post

## Step 1 — Create the MDX File

Create `src/content/trips/en/<slug>.mdx` where `<slug>` is lowercase, hyphenated (e.g. `thailand-pattaya-bangkok-phuket`).

### Required Frontmatter

```yaml
---
title: "Country/Place — Subtitle"
description: "1-2 sentence summary"
date: YYYY-MM-DD          # trip start date
location: "City, State/Country"
country: "Country"
category: "india" | "international"
region: "e.g. North India, Southeast Asia"
duration: "X days"
totalCost: 40000           # per person, number only
currency: "INR"
coverImage: "/images/trips/<slug>/cover.jpeg"
gallery: []
tags: ["tag1", "tag2"]
featured: true
draft: false
locale: "en"
accommodation:
  - name: "Hotel Name"
    costPerNight: 1300       # number
    rating: 4                # 1-5
    bookingLink: "https://..."  # valid URL or omit entirely
    mapsLink: "https://..."     # valid URL or omit entirely
    pros: ["pro1", "pro2"]
    cons: ["con1"]              # can omit if none
---
```

### Schema Rules (will fail build if violated)

- `bookingLink` / `mapsLink`: must be a valid URL or omitted. **Never use empty string `""`**.
- `rating`: must be between 1 and 5.
- `category`: must be exactly `"india"` or `"international"`.
- No extra fields in accommodation objects (e.g. don't add `currency`).
- Use Google Maps links in `mapsLink`, booking/Airbnb/Klook links in `bookingLink`.

## Step 2 — Write the Content

Follow this structure (see existing posts for examples):

1. **Intro paragraph** — who, when, vibe of the trip
2. **"Before You Go"** section (visa, SIM, money exchange tips)
3. **Day-by-day sections** with `## Day N — Title` and `**Date**` subheading
4. **"What It Cost" table** — per person breakdown
5. **"Things to Know"** bullet list — practical tips
6. **"Final Thoughts"** — honest summary

### Image Tags

```html
<figure>
  <img src="/images/trips/<slug>/1.jpeg" alt="Description" class="rounded-xl" />
  <figcaption class="text-sm text-center text-charcoal-light mt-2">Caption text</figcaption>
</figure>
```

## Step 3 — Add Images

1. Create directory: `public/images/trips/<slug>/`
2. Add a `cover.jpeg` and numbered photos (`1.jpeg`, `2.jpeg`, etc.)
3. **Convert HEIC/PNG to JPEG** before adding (browsers can't display HEIC):
   ```bash
   sips -s format jpeg photo.HEIC --out photo.jpeg
   ```
4. **Compress for web** (max 1600px wide, 75% quality):
   ```bash
   sips --resampleWidth 1600 -s format jpeg -s formatOptions 75 photo.jpeg --out photo.jpeg
   ```
5. Target: each image under 500KB, cover under 1MB.

## Step 4 — Publish

```bash
git add -A
git commit -m "Add <trip-name> trip post with photos"
git push origin main
```

Vercel auto-deploys from `main`. Check the deployment at the Vercel dashboard.

## Checklist

- [ ] Frontmatter passes schema (no empty bookingLinks, valid rating, correct category)
- [ ] All images are JPEG (not HEIC/PNG/JPG uppercase)
- [ ] Images compressed (under 500KB each)
- [ ] Cover image set and exists
- [ ] `draft: false` if ready to publish
- [ ] Cost table totals match `totalCost` in frontmatter
- [ ] Pushed to `main` for Vercel deployment
